  "text": "The attenuated Salmonella phoP/phoQ strains and PQ-PCDNA3.1 plasmids were available in our laboratory. The ER gene with the GenBank accession number NM-001437 was used in the present study. PCDNA3.1-ER plasmid was constructed in our laboratory. The attenuated Salmonella phoP/phoQ strain was used as the vector to carry the PCDNA3.1-ER plasmid. The PCDNA3.1-ER plasmid was then transduced into the attenuated Salmonella phoP/phoQ strain by electroporation (2.5 kV, 25 mF, 200 Ω, pulse time 0.03 s) [CITATION_1] . The plasmid in the Salmonella transfectant was extracted to verify the successful transfection. The product was then subjected to agarose electrophoresis for visualization.",
